13th Avenue, east side, from W. 26th to 27th Streets, showing the skeletal frame work of the new Starrett-Lehigh Building. This massive building will occupy the entire block, extending eastward to 11th Avenue.
Note on the left of View 1, the southerly side of the Central (Terminal) Stores building. This stands on the block to the north.

April 22, 1931
Views 1,2

P. L. Sperr

Thirteenth Ave., east side, from and including West 24th to 25th Streets, showing in the background, the Baltimore and Ohio R.R. freight station and warehouse, located on the south side of West 26th Street, and beyond, the Starrett Lehigh Building, from West 26th to 27th Streets, and extending eastward to Eleventh Ave.

May 5, 1936.

P. L. Sperr.
